item.title: CVE-2021-4238|2024-08-03T17:23:10.165Z -- github.com%2Fmasterminds%2Fgoutils -- github.com%2Fmasterminds%2Fgoutils
item.description: Randomly-generated alphanumeric strings contain significantly less entropy than expected. The RandomAlphaNumeric and CryptoRandomAlphaNumeric functions always return strings containing at least one digit from 0 to 9. This significantly reduces the amount of entropy in short strings generated by these functions.
